<div align='center'><font size='4'><b>SUMMER FASHION FORECAST</b></font><br>
<img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/news_dress_2007-06-14.jpg' border='1'>
</div>
<div id='gazette_byline''><em>By Loretta Rivers<br><a href=http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1>Clothing Store</a> owner</em></div>
<b>Thursday, June 14, 2007</b> &mdash; Greetings, my dear citizens! I&#039;m happy Audrey&#039;s asked me to write another article. I&#039;ve had a lot of people come up to me on the street and ask, &quot;When will there be cool summer clothes in your store?&quot; Well, the answer is... today!<br><br>I&#039;m really into the trends this year. I&#039;ve designed simple, wearable clothes for boys and girls based on fashions I saw on runways all over the world! Well, that&#039;s not quite true. I saw pictures of the fashion shows in the insider magazines I get delivered to my house. Unfortunately, I won&#039;t be going to a big European fashion show anytime soon, because I have a fear of flying! But that&#039;s beside the point. Man, staying on topic in my writing is hard!<br>
<br>
So anyway, Millsberry is getting the Loretta Rivers version of what&#039;s hot to wear when it&#039;s hot out. For boys, it&#039;s out with plain, everyday hats, and in with bright visors or a printed baseball cap. Boys are also sporting comfy polos, T-shirts, and Hawaiian-print button-downs. Lightweight cotton is the way to go this season! And boys, don&#039;t forget to don a cool pair of shades to protect your eyes from that intense sun.<br><br>For girls, I&#039;ve designed soft sundresses for everyday wear. And of course, the classic tank is a must for summer. Let your feet breathe in cute sandals. And top off your outfit with some cool or funky sunglasses. We&#039;ve got a good selection at the store. Pair one of your favorite light-colored skirts with a cute t-shirt and you&#039;re totally summer-ready! Bright, springy colors are in.<br><br>Some other summer staples that I&#039;ve had in years past are coming back to the store, too. I&#039;m waiting for the shipments to come in, but check back soon so you can go on a shopping spree! See you at the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">Clothing Store</a>!</div>


<br><hr><br>

<div id='gazette_story'>
<div align='center'><font size='3'><b>MAKING WAVES</b></font><br>
</div>
<br>
Been to Sylvane Lake recently? Sylvie&#039;s still delighting citizens who are lucky enough to spot her. I&#039;ve been noticing some warm winds coming in from the lake that create beautiful rippling waves. It makes me think of my dad, who loves the ocean. Father&#039;s Day is this Sunday, June 17, so I&#039;ll be sending him a <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/post_office/?action=greetings&cat=Fathers%20Day">greeting card</a> for sure. <br><br>I sometimes miss the West Coast because I could see the Pacific Ocean from my house there. If only someone could bring the ocean to Millsberry!</div>
